grch38-constrained-coding-regions-quinla.summary: *LiftOver* Constrained Coding Regions (CCRs): https://www.nature.com/articles/s41588-018-0294-6. Regions of human specific coding constraint presumably under strong purifying selection. Constraint is based on the lack of variation within the gnomAD dataset calibrated by the size and CpG content of the region. Regional Constraint is broken up into Autosomes and the X-Chromosome. Chromosome coordinates and CCR regions are lifted over from GRCh37 to GRCh38 using the Crossmap algorithm. Any unmapped regions are removed. Any region split into multiple regions are combined. (NOTE: The genomic coordinates have been remapped, but there has been no QC on the CCR percentiles preservation. It is yet to be determined if the CCR percentiles have been completely preserved during the liftover, but it can be assumed they should be similar based on the little to no change in region sizes.)

hg19-repeatmasker-ucsc-v1.summary: RepeatMasker track from UCSC in bed format. Interspersed repeats and low complexity sequences identified using the RepeatMasker program. Scaffoldings missing from the GGD hg19.genome file are removed.

hg19-segmental-dups-ucsc-v1.summary: The hg19 segmental duplications (SuperDups) File from UCSC. That is, duplications of at least 1kb total sequence of non-repeatmasker sequence in bed format

hg19-simple-repeats-ucsc-v1.summary: Simple repeats track from UCSC. Simple tandem repeats and imperfect repeats identified by the Tandem Repeats Finder (TRF) algorithm. Any scaffoldings not in the hg19.genome file are removed from the final file

hg19-somatic-variants-ensembl-v1.summary: All known somatic mutations at the time of Ensembl release 75. Conseqeunces for each variant are included in the annotation. Decomposed and Normalized. Remapped from Ensembl GRCh37 to UCSC hg19. Ensembl variant info page can be found at: https://uswest.ensembl.org/info/genome/variation/index.html

hg19-structural-variants-ensembl-v1.summary: All known structural mutations at the time of Ensembl release 75. Remapped from Ensembl GRCh37 to UCSC hg19. Ensembl variant info page can be found at: https://uswest.ensembl.org/info/genome/variation/index.html

hg19-trna-genes-ucsc-v1.summary: tRNA gene predictions from tRNAscan-SE v1.23 hosted on UCSC.

hg38-bwa-1000g-v1.summary: pre-built bwa indicies from 1000g hg38/GRCh38 distribution

hg38-canonical-isoforms-ucsc-v1.summary: The Canonical Isofrom for each gene (or cluster) from UCSC. The APPRIS principal transcripts are used to define the canonical transcripts. If APPRIS filtering results in no transcripts, the longest isofrom is selected.

hg38-ccds-genes-ucsc-v1.summary: Consensus Coding Seqeunce (CCDS) high confidence gene annotation from UCSC. The annotation here are  high quality manually curated protein-coding regions from the Consensus CDS project.

hg38-chrom-mapping-ensembl2ucsc-ncbi-v1.summary: A tab delimited file containing scaffolding ids that maps GRCh38 Ensembl(GenBank) scaffoldings to hg39 UCSC scaffoldings. This is specific to patch 13 of the GRCh38 Human genome build. (1st column = Ensembl ids, 2nd column = UCSC ids)

hg38-chromsizes-ncbi-v1.summary: Chromosome lengths for the hg38 genome build from NCBI. (Used to create the Go Get Data (GGD) hg38.genome file)

hg38-clinically-associated-variants-ense.summary: All known clinically associated variants at the time of Ensembl release 99. Any variant in ClinVar classified as probably/likely-pathogenic, pathogenic, drug-response, or histocompatibility are included. Decomposed and Normalized. Remapped from Ensembl GRCh38 to UCSC hg19. Ensembl variant info page can be found at: https://uswest.ensembl.org/info/genome/variation/index.html

hg38-constrained-coding-regions-quinlan-.summary: *LiftOver* Constrained Coding Regions (CCRs): https://www.nature.com/articles/s41588-018-0294-6. Regions of human specific coding constraint presumably under strong purifying selection. Constraint is based on the lack of variation within the gnomAD dataset calibrated by the size and CpG content of the region. Regional Constraint is broken up into Autosomes and the X-Chromosome. Chromosome coordinates and CCR regions are lifted over from GRCh37 to GRCh38 using the Crossmap algorithm. Additionaly, the chromsomes have been remapped from Ensembl GRCh38 to UCSC hg38. Any unmapped regions are removed. Any region split into multiple regions are combined. (NOTE: The genomic coordinates have been remapped, but there has been no QC on the CCR percentiles preservation. It is yet to be determined if the CCR percentiles have been completely preserved during the liftover, but it can be assumed they should be similar based on the little to no change in region sizes.)

hg38-cpg-islands-ucsc-v1.summary: hg38 cpg islands from UCSC in bed format

hg38-cytobands-ucsc-v1.summary: Approximate locations of Chromosome Bands (cytoBands) located with Giemsa-stained chromosomes from UCSC

hg38-evofold-ucsc-v1.summary: *Liftover* The evolutionary conserved mRNA secondary structure predictions hosted on UCSC. In bed format. Lifted over from UCSC hg19 to UCSC hg38.

hg38-gaps-ucsc-v1.summary: Assembly gaps from UCSC in bed fromat

hg38-gene-features-ensembl-v1.summary: Gene features, including all annotated transcripts, that make up the Ensembl gene sets. (Alignment based annotation using proteins, cDNA, RNA-seq, etc.). Features are in GTF format. Remapped from Ensembl GRCh38 to UCSC hg38

hg38-gtf-ensembl-v1.summary: The GRCh38 gtf file from ensembl remapped to hg38 (Any unmapped entries are removed from the file)

hg38-gtf-refseq-ucsc-v1.summary: The UCSC RefSeq gene track converted into GTF format containing known human protein-coding and non-protein-coding genes from RefSeq. (RefSeq: NCBI RNA reference sequence collection) (UCSC GTF format info: https://genome.ucsc.edu/FAQ/FAQformat.html#format3)

hg38-known-genes-ucsc-v1.summary: The 'KnownGene' track from UCSC. Comprised of all gene models from GENCODE v32. Includes protein-coding genes, non-coding RNA genes, and pseudo-genes. Gene symbols and gene descriptions have been added to the dataset.

hg38-knowngene-gene-features-ucsc-v1.summary: Gene features from the 'KnownGene' track from UCSC. (GTF). Features include 5UTR, 3UTR, CDS, exon, start_codon, stop_codon, transcript. Features are comprised of all gene models from GENCODE v32. IDs correspond to the UCSC knowGene IDs.

hg38-microsatellites-ucsc-v1.summary: Microsatellites from UCSC. Region which tend to be highly polymorphic and with at least 15 di- or tri-nucletodie repeats

hg38-missense-z-score-exac-v1.summary: Missense Z Score by gene. A constraint score based on missense variation, from Samocha et al., Nature Genetics 2014. The score is derived by calculating a null expectation of missense variation for each gene, and comparing it to what is observed in ExAC, then stratifying each gene using a Z score distribution. That paper is at: https://www.nature.com/articles/ng.3050. Pseudo-liftover: Updated coordinates based on transcript ids that map between GRCh37 and GRCh38. If unable to map transcript id, the gene symbol is mapped between GRCh37 and GRCh38. If neither the transcript id or gene symbol map between the two builds the record is removed. Remapped from Ensembl GRCh38 to UCSC hg38

hg38-ncbi-refseq-gene-features-ucsc-v1.summary: Gene features for all curated and predicted annotations from the NCBI Refseq track from UCSC. (GTF). Refseq ALL. Human protein-coding and non-protein-coding genes from NCBI RNA reference seqeunce collection.

hg38-ncbi-refseq-genes-ucsc-v1.summary: NCBI Refseq Genes track from UCSC. Curated and predicated genes from Refseq. Data include protein-coding and non-protein-coding genes. Gene info includes chromosome, transcript coordinates, CDS coordinates, exon coordinates, exon count, strand, gene and transcript ids, etc.

hg38-ncbi-refseq-ucsc-v1.summary: The composite NCBI RefSeq gene track from UCSC converted to bed format. (Human protein-coding and non-protein-coding genes from NCBI RefSeq)

hg38-pfam-domains-ucsc-v1.summary: High quality, manually curated Pfam domain annotation in bed12 format from UCSC

hg38-phastcons-ucsc-v1.summary: Conservation scores based on the phastcons HMM algorithm against multi-aligned sequences of 100 different species

hg38-phenotype-associated-variants-ensem.summary: All variants at the time of Ensembl release 99 that have a known phenotype association. Decomposed and Normalized. Remapped from Ensembl GRCh37 to UCSC hg19. Ensembl variant info page can be found at: https://uswest.ensembl.org/info/genome/variation/index.html

hg38-radar-li-lab-stanford-v1.summary: **Liftover** Rigorously Annotated Database of A-to-I RNA Editing (RADAR). A comprehensive collection of Adenosine (A) to Inosine (I) editing sites in human transcripts, otherwise known as RNA editing sites. Paper: http://nar.oxfordjournals.org/content/42/D1/D109. Liftover from hg19 to hg38

hg38-reference-genome-ucsc-v1.summary: The hg38 reference genome from UCSC. This version includes the latest patch, patch 12. (url:http://hgdownload.soe.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/hg38/bigZips/p12/)

hg38-refseq-gene-features-ucsc-v1.summary: The UCSC RefSeq gene track converted into GTF format containing known human protein-coding and non-protein-coding genes from RefSeq. (RefSeq: NCBI RNA reference sequence collection)

hg38-repeatmasker-ucsc-v1.summary: RepeatMasker track from UCSC in bed format. Interspersed repeats and low complexity sequences identified using the RepeatMasker program.

hg38-segmental-dups-ucsc-v1.summary: Segmental duplications (SuperDups) File from UCSC. That is, duplications of at least 1kb total sequence of non-repeatmasker sequence in bed format.

hg38-sequence-1000g-v1.summary: Full hg38/GRCh38 reference genome distributed by 1000 genomes Derived from NCBI set with HLA and decoy alternative alleles ftp://ftp.1000genomes.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/ftp/technical/reference/GRCh38_reference_genome/

hg38-simple-repeats-ucsc-v1.summary: Simple repeats track from UCSC. Simple tandem repeats and imperfect repeats identified by the Tandem Repeats Finder (TRF) algorithm.

hg38-somatic-variants-ensembl-v1.summary: All known somatic mutations at the time of Ensembl release 99. Conseqeunces for each variant are included in the annotation. Decomposed and Normalized. Remapped from Ensembl GRCh38 to UCSC hg38. Ensembl variant info page can be found at: https://uswest.ensembl.org/info/genome/variation/index.html

hg38-structural-variants-ensembl-v1.summary: All known structural mutations at the time of Ensembl release 99. Remapped from Ensembl GRCh38 to UCSC hg38. Ensembl variant info page can be found at: https://uswest.ensembl.org/info/genome/variation/index.html

hg38-trna-genes-ucsc-v1.summary: tRNA gene predictions from tRNAscan-SE v1.23 hosted on UCSC.

mm10-reference-ucsc-v1.summary: Reference genome for mouse from UCSC
